<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./79: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-10T18:00:00-04:00">July 10,
                                    1934—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>152. Your 177 and 178, July 9. Our attitude on London naval conversations
                            and conference is expressed in our 141, June 27.<note n="38" xml:id="d124fn38">
                                <ref target="frus1934v01#pg_280">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 280</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Department has made no announcement, official or unofficial, relative to
                            matter of bilateral, non-aggressive pact with Soviet Union.</p>
                        <p>Your statement minimizes hope of effective negotiations with <persName corresp="#p_TAA1">Troyanovsky</persName>, but if and when he offers
                            to negotiate, we will canvass entire situation with him and endeavor to
                            impress him with the importance of speedy agreement as alternative to
                            dissolving bank and foregoing expectation of better trade relations
                            based upon assistance by our Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>